# Source pin for the documentation build's hash-locked requirements.
#
# WHY THIS EXISTS
# ---------------
# The docs CI job (.github/workflows/docs.yml) installs zensical with
# `pip install --require-hashes`, which demands a fully hash-pinned requirement
# set. OSSF Scorecard's Pinned-Dependencies check flags any unpinned `pip
# install`; hash-pinning closes that and makes the docs build tamper-evident.
#
# KEEP IN SYNC: this version must match the `zensical==` pin in pyproject.toml,
# so CI proves the exact version the published docs build uses.
#
# REGENERATE requirements/docs.txt after changing this file:
#   uv pip compile requirements/docs.in --universal --generate-hashes \
#       --python-version 3.13 -o requirements/docs.txt
zensical==0.0.47
